e have tackled other biggies so what about this one?<br>
<br>
Is it morally wrong to help end another person's life? Or is it morally wrong to prolong the life of someone suffering pain and anguish daily? <br>
<br>
Kim <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=powertotherae>Powertotherae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Satan's Lil' Minion</span><br>  Posts: 227<br> <font color=#3333ff>(3/5/03 11:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=144.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Assisted Suicide?</span><hr size=1> Obviously I do not have moral issue with this.<br>
<br>
As somebody who watched my 42-year-old mother die a slow and painful death from cancer I seriously thought about it when she was at her worst. There comes a point in cancer when no medication works and you are forced to watch someone you love moan and writhe in pain. You are then faced with the fact that person is not only going to die but die horribly and I personally wanted it to stop. Even though I wanted her to live and I think as her child some small part of me was thinking she should still pull out, that this was not happening. I couldn’t bare to see her crying (even though she was in a lite coma) and when we would clean her she would grimace. <br>
<br>
Before we brought her home to die she was in the cancer ward for 3 days. I stayed the whole time with her. It was the most horrible experience of my life. There were tons of forgotten people there in such pain that at night I couldn’t sleep cause all I could hear was people crying and screaming out in pain.<br>
<br>
I have no idea where this is going!!! I just think sometimes it would be more humane to not let people suffer.<br>
<br>
Leah <p>&quot;It ain't the parts of the Bible that I can't understand that bother me, it is the parts that I do understand.&quot; <br>
