But, I think that by crossing the line to assisted suicide we open the door to serious problems.  Unfortunately there are people out there who would use this loop hole to &quot;off&quot; an aging or sick family member just so they don't have to be burdened with the care.  I have seen enough abuse and heard about enough from colleaugues who work in the Adult protective services field to know that it would be more common than we can fathom.<br>
<br>
Since this is a board to &quot;debate&quot;/discuss religious topics, I will add that my personal faith based opinion is that only God should have the final say on when a person is to die.  When we take that into our hands, I think we are crossing a boundary that shouldnt be crossed.  <br>
<br>
I do think however that physicians are not doing enough to alleviate the pain in critically sick and dying patients out of fear of that those medications will actually speed up the dying process and thereby open themselves up to lawsuits.   - Shirene <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tupogirl>tupo girl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#3333ff>(3/6/03 3:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=144.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: assisted suicide</span><hr size=1> Shirene, you expressed more eloquently what I was trying to say. I think someone should be able to die naturally if they want. Ugh this sleep deprivation!<br>
