<br>
I believe people have a right to die. And to die with dignity. What is the dignity of wasting away in pain, soiling yourself, unable to get up from your bed, totally dependant on others for even a sip of water.<br>
<br>
There are some illnesses that even the strongest pain killers do not put a dent in the pain. <br>
<br>
And what if you come down with alztimers (sp)? I don't consider that to be living at the end. I would want to die. <br>
<br>
A person should have the right to choose. They should have to the right to choose to live and fight for life as well. Hey, you want everything done, by golly, everything should be done for you. And no one questions that wish. But prolonging someone's life when it isn't wanted or desired has been known to happen. <br>
<br>
How sad. <br>
<br>
On that note, not sure if any of you watch ER, if you do maybe you remember the episode where a 17 yo wanted an DNR but his mother wouldn't approve it. At what age do you think a minor is capable of saying, &quot;hey I have had enough&quot; and you let them go?<br>
<br>
Then I saw this on my yahoo news page about an older woman getting a <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://story.news.yahoo.com/news?tmpl=story&amp;ncid=573&amp;e=1&amp;cid=573&amp;u=/nm/20030306/od_nm/odd_widow_tattoo_dc" target="top">tatto</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> to make sure her wishes were known.<br>
